<HEAD>Two Young Brothers Found Dead in Freezer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MURFREESBORO, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two young brothers died after being
trapped in an abandoned freezer near their parents' home,
authorities said.
   The boys' stepfather, Larry O'Neal, found the bodies early
Monday in the freezer, which was about 100 yards from the home and
had been used as a worm bed, authorities said.
   Curtis O'Neal, 8, and his 5-year-old brother, Billy Joe, died
late Sunday or early Monday, said Pike County Coroner Dub Deal.
   Deal said the parents had last seen them flying a kite about 5
p.m. Sunday. When the boys didn't return home, the parents believed
they were spending the night with their grandparents, who live
nearby, he said.
   The boys' mother, Teresa O'Neal, discovered early Monday that
they were missing, the coroner said.
   Shirley Davis, the boys' grandmother, told authorities they may
have gotten muddy while playing in a creek and crawled into the
freezer to change clothes.
