<HEAD>A Chilly Night in the Northeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Wintry temperatures gripped the Northeast today as mild weather
prevailed over southern states.
   Temperatures were generally below freezing in the nation's
northeast quarter, with readings in the teens and single digits
over much of the Great Lakes region and the northern Atlantic Coast.
   A reading of 7 degrees shortly after midnight set a record in
Binghamton, N.Y. The old record low for the date was 8 degrees in
1965.
   In contrast, readings were in the 50s and 60s in the southern
and central Plains and the valleys and deserts of the Southwest.
Highs Monday were in the 80s.
   Wet weather was confined to widely scattered rainshowers in the
Northwest. Snow fell in some higher elevations, and snow advisories
were in effect for the Cascade Mountains, where 6 to 10 inches were
considered possible today and tonight.
   Clouds were over much of the Rockies, as well as the northern
Plains and the Northwest.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers in the Pacific
Northwest and southern Minnesota, possible snow in northern
Minnesota and scattered snow in northern Maine.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 50s or 60s across
much of the nation; the 20s across northern New England; the 30s
extending from the northern Great Lakes region into central and
southern New England; the 40s in northern Washington state, the
northern Rockies, the northern Plains, the upper Ohio Valley and
the Mid-Atlantic region; the 70s from the southern coast and
valleys of California to the southern Rockies, the lower half of
the Missouri Valley, the middle Mississippi Valley, the central
Gulf Coast and Florida; and the 80s from the desert Southwest to
southern Kansas, the southern Plains, the lower Mississippi valley
and Texas, with readings approaching 90 degrees from the central
Rio Grande Valley into the eastern Texas Panhandle.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from zero
degrees at Bradford, Pa., to 70 degrees at Palm Springs, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 58 fair; Boston 17 windy; Buffalo 14 cloudy;
Charleston, SC 51 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 29 fair; Cleveland 15
fair; Detroit 20 fair; Miami 58 fair; New York 20 windy;
Philadelphia 23 fair; Pittsburgh 17 fair; Portland, Maine 10 fair;
Washington 29 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 36 cloudy; Chicago 29 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
58 fair; Denver 47 cloudy; Des Moines 40 fair; Indianapolis 30
fair; Kansas City 51 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 34 fair; Nashville
44 fair; New Orleans 51 fair; St. Louis 44 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 43 fair; Anchorage 28 snow; Las Vegas 62
windy; Los Angeles 57 foggy; Phoenix 62 fair; Salt Lake City 50
cloudy; San Diego 58 cloudy; San Francisco 52 partly cloudy;
Seattle 42 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 9 fair; Toronto 9 fair.
</TEXT>
