<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wedding guests looked on in horror as a
suspected getaway car being chased by police ran down a bridesmaid,
dragged her across the street and smashed into the church where the
wedding had just taken place.
   Marilyn York, 18, of Little Rock, was helping to decorate the
bride and bridgroom's car Monday when she was hit and killed,
police said.
   She had been a bridesmaid in the wedding of 21-year-old Valarie
Dodson and 20-year-old Larry Charles minutes before at Hoover
United Methodist Church.
   Police were chasing a sports car which had been reported stolen
last week when the car was driven onto a parking lot and hit the
parked car onto which the wedding party had painted the words
``Just Married.''
   The speeding car then ran over Ms. York, crossed the street and
hit a corner of the church.
   The driver of the car ran a short distance and was caught and
arrested.
   ``We were decorating the car and spraying it when we heard a
loud noise,'' said Viola Dodson, the bride's mother. ``We had our
backs turned and when we looked around, we saw him coming at us
real fast.''
   The bride's mother said she started pushing people out of the
way and managed to get out of the path of the car herself.
   Ms. York, a friend of the bride, ``got caught between his car
and my car and he drug her body across the street and slammed into
the wall,'' Mrs. Dodson said.
   The police said the Firebird was reported to have been used as a
getaway car in a shoplifting at a Little Rock store Sunday and was
seen by a police officer less than a mile from the wedding scene
Monday. The officer tried to stop the car but the driver sped away.
