<HEAD>Baptist World Alliance Director Dies In California Car Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gerhard Claas, general secretary of the
Baptist World Alliance, has died from injuries sustained in a
traffic accident near Lodi, Calif., the alliance announced Tuesday.
   Claas, 59, was the chief administrative officer of the alliance,
an international Baptist organization which has a membership of
more than 35 million worldwide. The organization conducts teaching,
development and disaster relief efforts in Third World nations.
   Claas was traveling in California to a series of fund-raising
meetings when the car in which he was riding collided Monday with a
truck on a rural road in San Joaquin County near Lodi, 80 miles
northeast of San Francisco.
   He died later in the day. Two other people, the Rev. Mervyn
Betts, 74, and his wife Nora, 67, of San Francisco, also were
injured, sheriff's deputies said.
   Claas was a citizen of West Germany, where he had served in a
number of pastoral and administrative posts.
   Claas is survived by his wife, the formed Irmgard Saffran, of
McLean, Va., and three children: Regina, Gabriele Claas Gloeckner,
and Martin, who live in West Germany.
</TEXT>
