<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A federal judge has threatened to fine Eastern
Airlines $10,000 per day for future breaches of a court order that
has blocked the carrier from trying to sell its profitable East
Coast air shuttle.
   U.S. District Judge John H. Pratt also on Monday ordered Eastern
to halt its efforts to gain federal permission to complete the
proposed deal.
   Pratt wrote that in attempting to sell its shuttle, Eastern had
engaged in ``deliberate and intentional conduct'' that violated a
ruling the judge issued last summer. That July 2 order had
forbidden the company from changing working conditions of 12,000
mechanics and other ground workers represented by one of the
airline's unions.
