   Eligible stockholders in six financially
troubled production credit associations in the Omaha, Neb., and
Spokane, Wash., districts will receive par value cash or credit for
their stock, the Farm Credit System Assistance Board says.
   Eric P. Thor, head of the board, said Monday the compensation
will go to those whose stock either was frozen or not retired at
par when the associations went into liquidation.
