<1ST_LINE>u f BC-BritainStocks     03-22 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain Stocks,0213</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Narrowly Mixed at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were narrowly mixed at midday
Tuesday, with trading depressed by declines in New York and Tokyo
and by the lack of institutional buying interest in the market.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange index of 100 stocks was off
3.6 points, or 0.2 percent, at 1,837.5.
   Volume was a modest 211.7 million shares, up from 191.7 million
shares at the same time a day earlier.
   The market remained locked in a narrow range on Tuesday with
institutions again reluctant to buy stock near the start of the
current extended trading account, dealers said. The small size of
individual share transactions indicated that Tuesday's trading was
dominated by private client orders rather than institutional
investors, they added.
   Investors have been reluctant to take major decisions at the
start of the three-week account which began last Friday, extended
from the normal two-week period to take in the Easter holiday
weekend.
   The London Stock Exchange divides trading into either two-week
or three-week periods for accounting purposes. Trades generally
must be completed within 10 days of a period ending.
   London share prices also were depressed Tuesday by previous
falls in New York and Tokyo, dealers said.
</TEXT>
