<1ST_LINE>u f AM-CSX-TotalMinatome     03-22 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CSX-Total Minatome,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>CSX to Sell Oil and Gas Unit to Total Minatome</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   CSX Corp. said Tuesday it has agreed to
sell its oil and natural gas exploration subsidiary to
Houston-based Total Minatome Corp. for $612 million.
   The sale of CSX Oil & Gas Corp. is expected to be completed in
about 30 days, said CSX Chairman Hays T. Watkins in a joint
announcement with Minatome President Jean-Pierre Donnet.
   The CSX subsidiary's principal operations are located in the
United States, mostly along the Gulf coasts of Texas and Louisiana,
and in the North Sea.
   Total Minatome is involved in exploration and production in
Wyoming, Oklahoma, the Gulf Coast and the Gulf of Mexico. It is a
wholly-owned subsidiary of Total Compagnie Francaise des Petroles,
which is based in France.
   The deal will allow Total Minatome a chance to expand its U.S.
and North Sea operations and is in keeping with CSX's plan to
concentrate on its primary transportation, pipeline, property and
technology groups, Donnet and Watkins said.
</TEXT>
