<HEAD>Sears Begins Tender Offer for Western Auto Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sears, Roebuck and Co. said Tuesday it has begun
its $19-a-share tender offer for all outstanding common stock of
Western Auto Supply Co.
   The tender offer expires April 18, unless extended.
   As previously reported, directors and management of Western Auto
have agreed to sell to Sears 52.3 percent of the outstanding shares
upon completion of the tender offer.
   Sears said the deal is expected to cost $250 million for the
stock, plus $152 million in assumed debt.
